OL,3,CAuthorities repeatedly warned about
OL,4,Cterrorist's mental health, inquest
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FHe had attended a drop in session and
OL,8,Fwanted information on how to claim
OL,9,Fasylum. He also told support workers
OL,10,Fthat he was a child soldier in Libya.
OL,12,FDuring a support session in November
OL,13,F2016, the charity became concerned
OL,14,Fabout his mental health when he told
OL,15,Fthem he wanted to return home to fight.
OL,17,FSaadallah stormed out of the meeting
OL,18,Fand assaulted two members of the
OL,19,Fpublic on the street outside. He was
OL,20,Fsubsequently sent to prison.
